- I really enjoy seeing the happy faces of young students every day here at Five Hawks!
- Lived in Prior Lake with my wife and 3 children (now adults) since 1995.
- Love the outdoors ‚Äì Fishing, hunting, hiking, camping

post_text:
Our Feature Teacher this week is Rochelle Klamm. Rochelle has been heavily involved with Five Hawks PTC in the past but we are SO excited to have her on staff now! Welcome Mrs. Klamm.
‚ÄúThis will be my 8th year teaching for the Prior Lake-Savage Schools and my first year teaching at Five Hawks. My husband also works for Prior Lake and is a Tech Integrationist at Prior Lake High School. We have 3 kids, 2 of which go to Five Hawks and our oldest will start her first year at Twin Oaks Middle School. I have been involved with Five Hawks since our oldest was in kindergarten and I am so excited to now be teaching there.
When I am not at school I enjoy photography, baking, house projects, anything creative and being outside with my family. I am looking forward to working with many new families and helping everyone have an amazing and successful school year!‚Äù #fivehawkspride

post_text:
We would like to give our new staff a little ‚ÄúTeacher Feature‚Äù before school starts. Today we want to introduce you to a new 2nd grade teacher, Mrs. Susan Anderson. Let‚Äôs welcome Mrs. Anderson to our Five Hawks Family!

This is my 16th year in the Prior Lake Schools and my first year at Five Hawks. I am married and have 3 kids and 2 dogs! Two of my kids will be at Five Hawks this year. I have one child that is in preschool. We are very excited to meet everyone!

My passion is books and kids. I am known for my large collection of books for kids and getting books in kids hands. Stay turned for more information on this!

Over the summer, my family and I spent a lot of time at our cabin. We fished, went swimming, read a lot and spent a lot of time together. With this upcoming year and it‚Äôs many challenges, my goal is to get students to love to read and to find the right books for each child. #fivehawkspride

Jennifer Nemecek
April 24 at 12:31 PM ¬∑

Wednesday Morning Update!! Thanks to you, Lakers, we have raised over $2300 for R.O.C.K.! What an amazing community we have! There is no question that we are #LAKERSTRONG!

Hey Lakers!! Are you looking for a way to show off your Laker Pride now that we will be distance learning for the remainder of the school year?

We've designed these #LAKERSTRONG yard signs to help you show your support for our educators and recognize your Laker learners! They are $13/each (stake included) with $5 of every sign purchased donated to R.O.C.K. to help them continue their mission of supporting our community's kids' needs!

In order to purchase, please fill out this Google Form, which will give you the details regarding payment (Venmo preferred) and pick up (local Prior Lake residence). https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfQcEbXmPvC8St7DB0PH79pixR3xtg-eVY8ZUmtvX44mfdSHQ/viewform

PICK UP IS AFTER 12PM SATURDAY (4/25). The address is on the Google Form, but message me if you need it again! Thanks!

post_text: From a Five Hawks parent. Gave us chills to read! Thank you Mallori Nicewanner for putting into words what so many felt today!
shared_text:
Mallori Nicewanner
March 18 at 4:48 PM ¬∑

Went to pick up Ava‚Äôs school materials today. As we were driving away we rolled down the window to wave at her gym teacher. He said ‚ÄúBye, play every day!‚Äù ‚ù§Ô∏è I started crying.

I‚Äôm sad for my kids if their school year has ended and they are now missing their teachers, friends, social interaction, etc.

I‚Äôm sad for the teachers in all of this unknown. So, I‚Äôm sending all of my love to you teachers and throwing out a huge THANK YOU for all you have done, are doing and will continue to do for our children!
